elements.title: Isabel Leighton
elements.contents: ... that Isabel Leighton (pictured), an actress and writer, created a chair in hematology at Yale University in honor of her husband?

elements.title: Museum of Contemporary Art Australia
elements.contents: ... that the Museum of Contemporary Art Australia is the only contemporary art museum in the country with a permanent collection?

elements.title: Banzai Bug
elements.contents: ... that the Windows 95 game Banzai Bug, in which a player controls a bug that must escape from an exterminator's house and is told as a war story, was created as "The Flight-Sim with an Attitude"?

elements.title: Jérôme Chappellaz
elements.contents: ... that Jérôme Chappellaz wants to collect ice cores from Africa's Mount Kilimanjaro to be preserved in Antarctica?

elements.title: Stenoperla prasina
elements.contents: ... that the New Zealand stonefly Stenoperla prasina was the five millionth specimen digitised by the Natural History Museum in London?

elements.title: Robert A. Emmitt
elements.contents: ... that shortly after getting married in 1875, Robert A. Emmitt crossed the Cascade Mountains driving a cattle herd while his wife led a pack horse that carried their possessions?

elements.title: Zigzag House
